rComments: Very organized professor and a wonderful person. Her course outlines are almost 25 pages with rubrics for each and every deliverable so whoever says its not clear has not read the syllabus. If you don't follow instructions or take multiple reminders seriously or ask for extension on time, she is not flexible on accepting late work.

A decent teacher might try to make her slides less complicated. The course is relatively simple but the teacher will tend to make it more complicated especially her exams. She may seem harsh but she is really nice as long as you work.

She is a great professor and very fair, I have never had anyone so accommodating and felt many students were trying to get advantage by not submitting work on time. She eventually started refusing any late assignment without extension requests and that made lazy ones unhappy. I would definitely take her courses as I learned a lot.

The course is fairly easy but the prof is very difficult to deal with. She tries to make things unnecessarily difficult. Her replies to emails are rude and unprofessional. Does not follow a clear grading scheme and does not clarify feedback on assignments. Avoid her if you can. The class is easy. It's not worth it putting up with her behavior.

Probably the worst prof I've had so far. She's very unprofessional and arrogant. The lectures are very bland and just reads off of her slides which are of little to no help to learn the actual course material. Definitely would not recommend.
She might be an amazing professor in person but for an online class, her recording lectures are not useful for her exams. Her slides are also not very useful for the exams either.
don't understand why she got such a good rating... her slides contain 0 useful information and tough exams...

Very easy to follow, lectures were extremely well structured and delivered; she is obviously passionate about the course. Very accommodating and understanding. I would definitely take courses with her.

This professor is top notch. I can not say enough good things about her. She is incredibly well spoken. She explains concepts and is firm but fair. HIGHLY HIGHLY recommend taking any class that she is instructing.
She was my favourite professor this and last semester. Her group case assignments weren't too harsh and the material was clear. Would definitely take her again as a prof if I can in the future.

This Prof is a walking library, I am a mature student and have many degrees already. I must say I am impressed with her knowledge and social skills. Very humble and down to earth person but has no issue being blunt either. Very clear in her expectations, very organized. Faculty needs more professors like her.

I look forward to seeing if I can take more classes with her in the future  this was my only in person class last semester and she made it worth coming to campus. I really enjoyed her teaching method. She was kind and understanding throughout the whole semester and I appreciate how she gave us a say in certain parts of the course when she could.
I had this prof last semester online, and this semester in person. She knows the content she's teaching incredibly well and is an engaging teacher. I always enjoy her classes!
Amazing professor! Super involved in everything and loves helping her students achieve their goals. Truly one of the best professors I've ever had.

I think I would have enjoyed this class even more if we had it in person. I think that the prof is really sweet and puts in a lot of effort in her lectures. As long as you put in the work and understand the material you should be good for the midterm and final.

Not a bad prof, but get ready for 3+ hour long recordings of a 1.5 hour class, with lots of irrelevant rambling/extremely slow talking. Slides offer very little information so you'll probably have to read the textbook if you wanna do good. Lots of easy group projects to grade boost though.

Such an amazing professor. The lectures are interesting and nice to attend. However, the professor does use PowerPoint presentations to present lectures. Sometimes the slides has little to no information on them so you must pick up key information. Other than that, the professor is a real gem. Differently recommend.

She is a fair prof. I remember telling her I took her class after reading comments. she laughed and said make sure to attend sessions, ask questions otherwise you would be among those who would go online to rant after getting their final grade. Now I know what she meant, good comments during the semester and bad comments after the final exam :D

She rounded grades if people were 1-2 points to the higher grade. I emailed assuming I might have done better and was embarrassed to see she made my 72.3 a grade B into a B+ and as far as I know she did that to the whole class. Show up for live sessions, ask questions or you would bomb exams if you rely on memorizing.
Easy class but she made the multiple choices too similar and if they weren't then they were textbook content. Someone said she is not into pleasing anyone and that is so accurate.

Very caring and friendly prof. Cares about her students and puts a lot of effort into her lectures. Lectures are 100% necessary. Fair exams. Its my third course with her and I intend on taking her courses if they are in my concentration.

This professor was the best one I have EVER had in my many years as a student. I had her for many classes during my undergrad. For those who complain about having her, I am sure she feels the same way about you, only you don't have a page on which she can put her thoughtful commentary :)

Great prof! really good discussion and made the class interesting despite covid. Not a difficult course, content was very manageable. probably the only professor this semester that really showed how much she actually cares for students.

I personally find her very fair, and detail oriented. A wonderful person but she is very blunt and is not into pleasing anyone that is for sure. Very helpful and supportive if you put the effort and ask for assistance. Make sure to read instructions and what she posts online. Then you wouldn't have even a single question on anything.

The midterm was alright, the long answer really helped me get a decent mark, although the multiple choice questions in this class are extremely long with each including a paragraph case before the question. I wish the final wasnt only MC so I can better show my knowledge of the topic rather then being right or wrong every question.

rComments: My fav prof. She made boring material interesting, loved her input on HR issues apart from lecture material. Probably one of the best profs at Telfer, highly recommend.

Her sections remained full, I couldn't get in. My roommates were in her section, I knew her as a prof so listened to her lectures not my prof's. Great teacher, shares feedback clearly and is pretty clear on what expectations are. What's on the slides and the book is on the midterms and exams, no surprises. Quick to responding to emails to clarify things and makes sure to share announcements so students don't get lost.

Professor Shaukat really made the class unnecessarily difficult. Her International Training and Development for Sustainability class initially sounded like a unique concept and I went into it with the hopes of learning something interesting. Good Professor, made cross-cultural course interesting. Cases studies are tough and long. Exam was all based on lectures so religiously go through her lectures. Reading book alone will not help. The prof uses asynchronous lectures that makes a course which could be interesting, incredibly boring. Assigns case studies that take endless research and endless time because they are so unrelated to course material and marked very harshly.

I am enjoying the course. I can go through course material and tons of resources professor shares every week as many times I want to. Prof should make attendance mandatory.
Lectures are pre-recorded and the prof's voice cuts out regularly which makes the class boring and unmotivating. As well, don't expect the prof to respond with more than one-word answers.

Great teacher, shares feedback on cases and is pretty clear on what expectations are. What's on the slides and the book is on the midterms and exams, no surprises. Quick to responding to emails to clarify things and makes sure to share announcements so students don't get lost. She takes the time to talk to students after the live sessions are over.
Exceptional professor, expectations are very clear and wants everyone to do well. Exams and assignments are very straight-forward. Highly recommend this professor!

Rumaisa was a very good professor to have for International Business. The lecture content is dry but she tries to relate the topics to real world examples that are currently happened. Really nice professor who cares about her students. Very content heavy course but her lectures are engaging and well thought out.

My favourite professor, hands down. Extremely kind and conveys information in such a clear, concise way. Clearly loves what she does and takes her job seriously. Was really empathetic about the switching online situation- extremely responsive, understanding, and helpful. I wish she taught every class!!

A wonderful prof! Very patient and fair. Makes the class very enjoyable and always willing to go above and beyond for students . If you are in a habit of missing classes and expect a good grade just by going with lecture or book, forget about that. She tests on what she covers in the class. Also took HR and OB with her and loved her classes.

Excellent professor, takes the time to answer every single question. Didn't feel like I took an online class. Her lectures are detailed and during live sessions she welcomes questions. I had to write this as the comment below is wrong at all levels. seems like someone who didnt attend live sessions and did bad and decided to rant here.

I don't usually write reviews but I made an account just for this. Worst prof I've had in my four years at university. All her lectures were pre-recorded with minimal live contact. She's not the most interesting but she explains everything clearly and the class is fairly easy to get a good grade. You do most of your work with a group. She's pretty decent.

She's one of the best teachers I've ever had. Plus she's very accessible outside class sessions (even with the online class). Answers emails with patience. I admire this professor's patience more than anything. She is an amazing human being. She caught people cheating and gave them a chance to either drop the class or face consequences. One of the best professors. Very easy to talk to. Very detailed lectures that help you understand content very well. She is kind, patient and absolutely supportive. Very fair exam. I will take courses with her for sure.

An awesome professor very fair. Very patient and accommodating. Awesome Professor, easily to tell that she is very passionate about what she teaches in class. Always calm and understanding and encouraging. Her examples are funny yet linked to topics! I love her, you would love her too :)

Great speaker. She explains the material extremely well and in a way that's engaging. Really cares and gets to know her students. She is a very fair marker and clearly outlines what you need to know in order to well. Attend her lectures as they often indicate what topics are important.

A wonderful professor! Always comes in 30 to 45 minutes early for the class and leaves late, she is always available to help. Great prof, learned a lot! Recommend taking this class with her.

She is an amazing professor. one of the best classes I have had. very strict about punctuality and class preparation, very blunt about her position. read your book is very important because she doesn't teach a lot from the lecture.

A wonderful professor, clear about her expectations right from the beginning. It was my third class with her and I liked the way she organizes her courses. She is easy to talk to and she cares about students. Highly recommended!

Study the textbook!
Amazing Professor! Best prof I have ever had in my university career! Highly recommended. Final Exam is hard if you do not read the book or pay attention in class.
Great Prof. Enjoyed all my 4 classes with her. AM graduating now but would love to take her classes if I am back for graduate studies.
My favourite prof at OttawaU. Do take classes with her :)

At times lengthy lectures get boring but  I wont blame the professor. she is great, very student oriented and does a good job in making course material comprehendible. She sure is very straight forward so no nonsense or dumb questions which means read the course outline before emailing...
Great class, and she made the boring methodology course simple for us. I will for sure take courses with her in the future.
Great prof, like her lectures as they are much more than the textbook. A nice person as well!
Great professor, humble, kind, and very approachable. Cares about students and always answers any questions, surprisingly remembers most of the names. I enjoyed both of my courses with her.
Very clear, approachable, caring and knowledgeable professor. I always did well in her classes because I never missed any classes.

Am taking a course now as well but my comment is based on my experience last year. she is one of the best profs, teaching many different courses and in each course you feel like this must be her area of expertise or what she really enjoys....she is that good :)
Excellent prof, very genuine person. Cares more for students. Wish more profs are humane like her. See is smart but doesn't show off as most of the profs do.
Excellent class, lengthy lectures but I learn a lot. Will definitely take classes with her again.

She genuinely cares about her students and if she sees you put the effort in, has not problem taking extra time to meet with you and help you succeed. prof is respectful and insightful and explains concepts well. Doesn't read off the slides or the book.

I agree with most comments, her lectures are long but thorough, you don't even need the book as she makes it easy to understand difficult concepts. She sure is very knowledgeable and a nice person too.
Very brutal 3 hour lectures but if you can concentrate the whole time you can tell she knows what she's doing. Exam and Midterm very easy, just study her slides. Don't need the textbook.
Love her classes and love her too :)

I took ADM3339, ADM2337 and ADM3319 with her. Learning something from someone who knows what she is talking about WITHOUT depending on notes is rare. She is an excellent Prof, Telfer needs more people like her.

Great prof. She teaches mostly lecture-based courses so it does get a  bit boring. But you do learn a lot. It surprised me sometimes how she knows this much without reading notes like most of the profs do. Class was big but as far as I know everyone liked her.
Nice teacher, the midterm and final were both fairly easy. But for a 3 hour class it got pretty boring after a while, many people left by the break. Class was still easy though.

I enjoyed the course even though research methodology is not my thing. Prof. was very good in making it easy for us to understand. I liked the exam with more application type of questions, so memorizing the book won't take you anywhere unless you really know the content.

Great course and great professor. It was very practical courses, learned a lot of skills. Lectures were good, kept me awake even in my least favorite time of the day 8am. TA was bad but professor was kind enough to re-evaluate. SHe is the best professor at Telfer!

Do not miss her lectures if you want to pass the course. Make sure to read course outline before asking her to explain anything already in there. I didn`t feel like having any question on any assignment as many others because I DID read the outline and course expectations. Yuhuuuuuuuuuuu

I always find it interesting to read what people write about profs right after the final exam. We had an exam last night for CMN2101 and it was tough but not unfair. She is a good prof, very kind and supportive. Some people just need a life and be honest in commenting on others. with all due respect,

I don't normally write comments but I found recent two comments totally unfair. She is the only profit reputation as a student oriented person. She is a horrible prof and was very difficult to understand. She did not answer questions in person or over email if she felt they were repetitive. She was very rude. Rambles and never takes a breath when talking. Course was easy, assignments, midterm... simple. I like her, managing a class with 250+ students is not easy for even senior profs. She is a good human and easy to talk to.

She seems to ramble on about topics and after awhile the information is useless which makes her lectures extremely boring and hard to listen and pay attention to. The class itself is mostly common sense. I also find she can be very rude at times

She is extremely friendly and you can have a conversation with her. She is helpful and answers questions anytime through email or in person. Her class is kind of boring but thats probably because of the content of the class. Her exams and assignments arent hard but her TAs are kind of tough markers.
Fair and a good lecturer. One of the rare profs I was able to follow and not fall asleep :) OttawU needs more people like her but I heard she will be leaving OttawaU next year.
knowledgeable, fair and helpful but a bit strict :)
The best prof ever!

A very dedicated prof and a decent person. I had 5 coruses with her over the period of 4 years. I kind of stalk her on university web site to see what she is teaching. Keep good class notes.

Very interesting and engaging class. I learned a lot from this course. I will definitely take another course with this prof. If possible.

Easy prof but she is so incredibly boring. Reads right off the slideshow which made it almost unnecessary to go to class. She also has a habit of going over the simple topics more than necessary.

not the most enthusiastic of people ahah but she is fair, knowledgable, and VERY organized. her syllabus is very thorough so you know exactly what to do/expect in terms of projects and exams. had her 3 times now and like her class structure every time as its fairly similar.
Great prof. Very knowledgeable and approachable. Very flexible adn accommodates pretty much all students.

Both Thumbs up, very smart and highly qualified person. Learned a lot in her class. She just need to pretend that she can tolerate nonsense.
excellent professor!

i enjoyed the course and professor. She was however annoyed at students' attitude in summer. This is my third class with her and I would love to take any other class she offers. FOr people who miss classes and are not serious for studies, dont take her class!

Very easy to get marks through assignments in this class, but the exams are fairly tough. he prof herself is very difficult to understand, and is very unhelpful, not offering much help outside of class at all. Avoid this prof if it is not completely necessary for your program.

Spends too much time on each powerpoint slide (even if the concept is straightforward). Everything is very easy until the final exam - confusing wording. Brought my mark down a full letter grade (not because I was unprepared!) I would recommend choosing a different professor.
One of the best profs I had at the university, knowledgeable, kind , fair and realistic. Very organized and clear about her expectations.

Pros:1)Very kind,smart, likeable 2)very professional and knowledgeable. High expectations, but specific about what she wants/Overall good lecturer/Learned a great deal in her class/Don't come late

Very easy, kinda boring but shes really nice and always willing to help, i recommend you take  a class with her if you have the chance...
